      [
        ":h1",
        {
          "s": "Hob View Conversion Tracker"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Tracking progress of converting JS views to Hob on the "
        },
        [
          ":code",
          {
            "s": "hob-views"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " branch."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":h2",
        {
          "s": "North Star"
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "Hob should be the obvious choice for "
        },
        [
          ":em",
          {
            "s": "any"
          }
        ],
        {
          "s": " user-programming within Hobson. There should be no reason to choose JS except for familiarity. Hob — and its integration with Hobson (item references, code-as-data, structural editing, queryable AST) — should be better than JS for most things, and as good for the rest."
        }
      ],
      [
        ":p",
        {
          "s": "This reframes the remaining work. The goal is not \"add enough primitives to convert the remaining views\" — it's to make Hob genuinely superior for Hobson programming. Every primitive should be designed so that Hob is what you'd choose even if you knew JS perfectly."
        }
      ],
